    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Tongue Grab",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>If the boggard champion hits a creature with its tongue, that creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed} by the boggard. Unlike with a normal grab, the creature isn't @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized}, but it can't move beyond the reach of the boggard's tongue. A creature can sever the tongue by hitting AC 30 and dealing at least [[/r {25}[slashing]]]{25 slashing Damage}. Though this doesn't deal any damage to the boggard, it prevents it from using its tongue Strike until it regrows its tongue, which takes a week.</p>"
        },
